messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
Somebody just shot a police officer!
Okay, what's the address, ma'am?
He's right in front of 14th Street behind the shopping center.
What shopping center, ma'am?
The one on Orange Blossom Trail.
Okay, what's your location exactly?
He's directly across from me. Please, I don't know if he's still there. Oh god!
Okay, who is it? Who got shot?
It's a police officer. I don't know the car number.
Is he down, or what?
He's down, he's down, he's flat down. He got three shots.
He got three shots?
Yes, ma'am. I'm just... I'm telling you right now.
Okay. Tell me where he is exactly.
You know where the library is on Orange Blossom Trail? He's directly in the back of there on Forty Fifth Street.
The library on Orange Blossom Trail?
Yes, 45th Street.
45th Street. Okay, hold on just a second. Ma'am, is he still in the car?
No, he's on the ground. He was out of the car doing a traffic stop.
He was doing a traffic stop?
Yes, and the next thing I know I heard three shots.
Okay. What kind of truck was it?
It's a white pickup truck. I don't know the number. Like a four-door pickup truck.
Is it a four-door?
I didn't pay much attention because it just looked like a traffic stop, so I went back inside.
Alright. Do you see the officer out there?
The police officer is on the ground, the pickup is gone. The guy shot him, put the gun back in his jacket, and he left.
Was the shooter a white male, black male?
He was a white male. About six feet tall, stocky build.
Hold on just a second. Stay on the line. Is he dead?
Oh my God. I don't know. I didn't walk across to him. Another police officer just arrived.
Okay, and they are checking on him now?
Yes, another officer is here. They're telling everyone to stay back.
Alright. Can you tell me more about the shooter?
He was wearing a white or creamish-colored jacket and dark pants.
Did you see what kind of gun he had?
I didn't see the gun clearly. I just heard the shots.
Okay. What is your name, ma'am?
I'm too scared to think straight. Can you just send help, please?
Help is already on the way. Just stay with me, okay?
Is there a deputy there now?
Yes, they're here. I think they are handling it now.
Alright, thank you for your information. Stay safe, ma'am.
